TITLE: imv
DESCRIPTION:
Global national 2020 demographic indicators for the world’s countries with a minimum population of 5,000 in 2020: total population, growth rate percent, life expectancy at birth, and infant mortality rate.

The values are from the U.S. Census Bureau International Data Base (IDB). Total population is for both sexes and all age ranges combined. Growth rate percent is the percent change in population during 2020 resulting from births, deaths, and international migration. This rate may be positive or negative. Life expectancy in years at birth for both sexes. Infant mortality rate is the number of deaths of infants under 1 year of age for both sexes per every 1,000 live births.

TITLE: Denver Region UAA by Tract
DESCRIPTION:
This layer is provided for Denver/Dallas region operational staff to view Undeliverable as Addressed (UAA) rates by tracts. This layer also contains information about the Type of Enumeration Area (TEA) makeup of each tract (i.e. all TEA 1, all TEA 6, or a mix of both). 

This layer contains both an "expected UAA rate" and "actual UAA rate". If the actual is lower than the expected rate, this is not a reason for concern. Reasons for a high UAA rate might include: seasonal occupancy, high vacancy rates, low mail delivery, or operational issues (printing or delivery errors).
